71
00:03:46,331 --> 00:03:48,249
Don't eat too quickly, okay?

72
00:03:48,333 --> 00:03:50,376
Do you know how hard it is
to age this for seven years?

73
00:03:50,460 --> 00:03:51,627
We need a photo of this.

74
00:03:51,711 --> 00:03:54,547
The "2018" faded a bit,
so it looks like "2016."

75
00:03:56,049 --> 00:03:57,383
Hey, hold it steady.

76
00:03:57,467 --> 00:03:59,344
I need a good shot of the date.

77
00:04:03,348 --> 00:04:04,307
What's that?

78
00:04:04,390 --> 00:04:05,391
What are you doing?

79
00:04:05,475 --> 00:04:06,851
Just hold on a second.

80
00:04:06,934 --> 00:04:08,436
TOP 10 TV SHOWS IN SOUTH KOREA
I'LL LOVE ANYONE THIS WINTER

81
00:04:08,978 --> 00:04:10,355
It's a hit.

82
00:04:10,438 --> 00:04:12,482
<i>I'll Love Anyone This Winter</i>
topped the streaming charts.

83
00:04:13,441 --> 00:04:15,401
-<i>Congratulations to you</i>
-Congratulations.

84
00:04:15,485 --> 00:04:17,320
<i>Congratulations to you</i>

85
00:04:17,403 --> 00:04:19,155
<i>-Congrats on topping the streaming charts</i>
-Congratulations.

86
00:04:19,238 --> 00:04:21,532
<i>-Congratulations to you</i>
-Congratulations.

87
00:04:24,619 --> 00:04:26,954
I thought I'd calm down if I got drunk,
but I haven't.

88
00:04:28,122 --> 00:04:29,707
Has she lost her damn mind?

89
00:04:29,791 --> 00:04:31,542
The drama is out right now.

90
00:04:31,626 --> 00:04:34,545
So why did she post a couple photo
and pull people out of the story?

91
00:04:34,629 --> 00:04:35,671
Sure enough,

92
00:04:35,755 --> 00:04:37,757
someone commented, "Behave yourself."

93
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:39,175
So I liked the comment.

94
00:04:40,093 --> 00:04:42,553
Then she DMed me and chewed me out.

95
00:04:42,637 --> 00:04:44,347
-Did I do something wrong?
-No.

96
00:04:44,931 --> 00:04:46,891
The drama is out,
so she <i>should</i> behave herself.

97
00:04:46,974 --> 00:04:47,934
-Right.
-Right.

98
00:04:48,017 --> 00:04:49,060
Plus, it's a rom-com.

99
00:04:49,143 --> 00:04:50,937
-Exactly!
-You know what?

100
00:04:51,562 --> 00:04:52,855
When someone comes at us hard,

101
00:04:54,107 --> 00:04:55,358
our hearts sink, and we think,

102
00:04:55,441 --> 00:04:56,859
"Did I do something wrong?"

103
00:04:56,943 --> 00:04:58,486
We blame ourselves too easily.

104
00:04:59,654 --> 00:05:00,571
Self-reflection

105
00:05:01,572 --> 00:05:02,824
is the language of the weak.

106
00:05:03,616 --> 00:05:05,827
Have you ever seen bad people
reflect on their actions?

107
00:05:06,452 --> 00:05:07,703
Don't reflect on this.

108
00:05:08,204 --> 00:05:10,623
-Don't reflect.
-Right. I won't reflect.

109
00:05:10,706 --> 00:05:12,208
-I won't.
-Hey.

110
00:05:12,291 --> 00:05:14,335
You have to open your eyes.

111
00:05:14,419 --> 00:05:16,379
You can't do that with your eyes closed.

112
00:05:16,462 --> 00:05:17,755
What are you doing?

113
00:05:18,756 --> 00:05:19,715
Hey!

114
00:05:20,258 --> 00:05:22,176
-Oh jeez.
-Here.

115
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:24,220
Whatever.

116
00:05:29,308 --> 00:05:30,893
What's it to you where I am?

117
00:05:32,061 --> 00:05:34,021
-Who is it?
-Ms. Oh Jeong-hui.

118
00:05:34,605 --> 00:05:38,317
Ms. Oh Jeong-hui is no different
than any other mother, is she?

119
00:05:38,401 --> 00:05:40,361
I guess she also checks
what time her daughter will be home.

120
00:05:42,446 --> 00:05:45,199
Can I ask you something?
I'm genuinely curious.

121
00:05:47,535 --> 00:05:50,371
How's Ms. Oh's relationship
with her biological daughter?

122
00:05:51,998 --> 00:05:52,915
I don't know.

123
00:05:52,999 --> 00:05:54,417
Do they keep in touch?

124
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:55,501
I don't know.

125
00:05:55,585 --> 00:05:57,170
It's taboo to talk about her.

126
00:05:57,253 --> 00:05:58,296
Why?

127
00:05:58,379 --> 00:05:59,422
How should I know?

128
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:03,467
But I have a feeling

129
00:06:04,260 --> 00:06:05,845
that they ended on very bad terms.

130
00:06:06,637 --> 00:06:09,515
Not that divorces
usually end on good terms,

131
00:06:10,183 --> 00:06:11,642
but I think the daughter
took her dad's side.

132
00:06:13,352 --> 00:06:14,937
I'd like to see her, though.

133
00:06:17,773 --> 00:06:18,608
Why?

134
00:06:19,108 --> 00:06:20,026
Just because.

135
00:06:20,902 --> 00:06:22,737
She probably knows who I am,

136
00:06:22,820 --> 00:06:24,113
but I don't know who she is.

137
00:06:24,697 --> 00:06:26,073
Isn't that kind of unfair?

138
00:06:26,157 --> 00:06:27,909
It really is unfair.

139
00:06:27,992 --> 00:06:30,161
-Seriously.
-How old is she?

140
00:06:30,244 --> 00:06:31,996
I don't know anything.

141
00:06:32,079 --> 00:06:34,290
Oh, I know her name. It's Byeon Si-on.

142
00:06:35,249 --> 00:06:37,627
I once overheard her on the phone.

143
00:06:38,961 --> 00:06:40,546
-Byeon Si-on?
-Yeah.

144
00:06:41,589 --> 00:06:42,423
Wait.

145
00:06:43,591 --> 00:06:44,800
Byeon Si-on.

146
00:06:45,676 --> 00:06:46,510
Eun-a…

147
00:06:47,136 --> 00:06:49,931
Eun-a was going to change her name
to Byeon Si-on.

148
00:06:50,473 --> 00:06:51,474
What?

149
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:54,143
No, no, no.

150
00:06:54,227 --> 00:06:56,145
Nope. That's just wrong.

151
00:06:56,229 --> 00:06:57,063
Not Byeon Si-on.

152
00:06:57,647 --> 00:06:59,941
Byeon Eun-a has to stay Byeon Eun-a.

153
00:07:00,024 --> 00:07:01,108
-Byeon Eun-a.
-Yeah.

154
00:07:01,192 --> 00:07:03,194
-Byeon Eun-a is so much better.
-Right.

155
00:07:03,277 --> 00:07:05,321
-Right.
-Ms. Byeon Eun-a.

156
00:07:05,404 --> 00:07:08,407
Please don't become Byeon Si-on.

157
00:07:09,408 --> 00:07:11,327
-Byeon Eun-a!
-Byeon Eun-a!

158
00:07:11,410 --> 00:07:13,287
-Byeon Eun-a!
-Byeon Eun-a!

159
00:07:13,371 --> 00:07:14,789
-Byeon Eun-a!
-Byeon Eun-a!

160
00:07:14,872 --> 00:07:15,706
Hey.

161
00:07:16,332 --> 00:07:18,668
Let me hold onto that.

162
00:07:27,677 --> 00:07:28,803
DAYS LIKE THIS, DAYS LIKE THAT
POEMS BY HWANG JIN-MAN

163
00:07:28,886 --> 00:07:29,762
Come on.

164
00:07:29,845 --> 00:07:33,349
SOMEWHERE, A WRONG REMAINS
POEMS BY HWANG JIN-MAN

165
00:07:33,432 --> 00:07:35,351
Why do you keep messing with that?

166
00:07:35,434 --> 00:07:37,061
Do you want me to help you?

167
00:07:37,144 --> 00:07:38,729
Oh, well…

168
00:07:39,522 --> 00:07:40,481
This…

169
00:07:42,149 --> 00:07:44,652
SOMEWHERE, A WRONG REMAINS
POEMS BY HWANG JIN-MAN

170
00:07:48,197 --> 00:07:49,031
Oh.

171
00:07:49,907 --> 00:07:50,992
They don't look alike.

172
00:07:51,075 --> 00:07:53,119
POET HWANG JIN-MAN

173
00:07:53,202 --> 00:07:54,495
He's handsome.

174
00:08:28,279 --> 00:08:29,697
My feet are cold!

175
00:08:34,035 --> 00:08:36,287
Mi-ran, you have to come see this.

176
00:08:36,370 --> 00:08:37,747
-Come quickly and see this.
-Okay.

177
00:08:37,830 --> 00:08:39,457
This is really cool.

178
00:08:39,957 --> 00:08:41,959
I promise it's really cool. Just watch.

179
00:08:42,585 --> 00:08:44,337
All right, just watch.

180
00:08:45,463 --> 00:08:46,797
-Help him!
-Hey!

181
00:08:47,673 --> 00:08:49,675
-You know what this is, right?
-No.

182
00:08:49,759 --> 00:08:51,177
-Watch carefully, okay?
-Okay.

183
00:08:51,260 --> 00:08:53,179
-One, two, three!
-Two, three!

184
00:08:59,352 --> 00:09:02,271
-Merry Christmas!
-Merry Christmas!

185
00:09:02,355 --> 00:09:05,107
-Three, two, one!
-Three, two, one!

186
00:09:05,191 --> 00:09:06,233
Action!

187
00:09:07,860 --> 00:09:08,944
Merry Christmas!

188
00:09:27,421 --> 00:09:28,339
It's snowing.

189
00:09:54,782 --> 00:09:56,075
<i>I'm so happy</i>

190
00:09:57,493 --> 00:10:00,830
<i>to have relationships like this</i>
<i>where we can be crazy together.</i>

191
00:10:41,036 --> 00:10:44,498
KNOCK KNOCK KNOCK
BY MA JAE-YEONG, YEONG-SIL

192
00:10:52,590 --> 00:10:53,424
Good night.

193
00:11:15,738 --> 00:11:17,156
You're back. Eat before you wash up.

194
00:11:25,247 --> 00:11:26,207
Yes, sir?

195
00:11:26,832 --> 00:11:27,666
Oh.

196
00:11:27,750 --> 00:11:29,502
We're not starting right away.

197
00:11:30,544 --> 00:11:31,921
It'll take some time.

198
00:11:32,922 --> 00:11:33,964
We're still casting.

199
00:11:34,840 --> 00:11:35,925
Yes, of course.

200
00:11:36,717 --> 00:11:38,427
The end of the year
is peak catering season,

201
00:11:38,511 --> 00:11:39,512
so of course I'll work.

202
00:11:40,095 --> 00:11:41,096
Yes, sir.

203
00:11:41,180 --> 00:11:42,097
Salute!

204
00:11:47,686 --> 00:11:49,355
Don't get too caught up in life.

205
00:11:52,816 --> 00:11:54,360
Don't get caught up in happiness…

206
00:11:56,070 --> 00:11:57,613
or sadness either.

207
00:12:09,959 --> 00:12:11,418
Can't I get a little caught up?

208
00:12:12,294 --> 00:12:13,504
It's the first time I've been happy.

209
00:12:24,598 --> 00:12:27,059
Don't run the washing machine
early in the morning!

210
00:12:28,644 --> 00:12:30,938
The pipes are frozen,
so the water won't drain!

211
00:13:10,311 --> 00:13:11,687
CEO KO

212
00:13:17,234 --> 00:13:18,152
Why are you calling so early?

213
00:13:18,235 --> 00:13:19,236
<i>Ms. Ko.</i>

214
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:21,405
You need to work smarter than this.

215
00:13:22,197 --> 00:13:23,115
What's wrong with you?

216
00:13:24,617 --> 00:13:27,161
<i>I heard you gave Noh Kang-sik</i>
<i>Hwang Dong-man's screenplay.</i>

217
00:13:27,244 --> 00:13:29,038
<i>Did you do that</i>
<i>because you think you've got a shot?</i>

218
00:13:29,121 --> 00:13:30,372
Mr. Choi, do you like me?

219
00:13:30,456 --> 00:13:31,999
<i>Why do you keep pestering me?</i>

220
00:13:32,082 --> 00:13:34,209
<i>Do you regret our falling out?</i>

221
00:13:34,293 --> 00:13:35,628
I find it satisfying.

222
00:13:35,711 --> 00:13:36,962
<i>Watch what you say.</i>

223
00:13:37,046 --> 00:13:38,714
Pester you? When did I ever do that?

224
00:13:38,797 --> 00:13:40,716
Let's be clear,
you're the ones pestering me.

225
00:13:41,842 --> 00:13:45,346
You gave Noh Kang-sik that screenplay
just to get on my nerves.

226
00:13:45,429 --> 00:13:47,014
Please shut up

227
00:13:47,556 --> 00:13:49,266
<i>and mind your own business.</i>

228
00:13:49,350 --> 00:13:52,227
There are only so many top actors.
How am I supposed to avoid yours?

229
00:13:52,311 --> 00:13:54,271
I just pitch it everywhere I can
and take what sticks.

230
00:13:54,355 --> 00:13:56,857
-Hey.
<i>-If you call me again,</i>

231
00:13:57,566 --> 00:13:59,234
I'll assume you like me.

232
00:14:02,655 --> 00:14:03,781
It's too early for this.

233
00:14:07,660 --> 00:14:08,744
I want that satisfaction

234
00:14:09,370 --> 00:14:11,330
of slamming down the receiver,

235
00:14:11,914 --> 00:14:14,375
but I can't get that with a cell phone!

236
00:14:14,458 --> 00:14:15,376
That son of a--

237
00:14:15,459 --> 00:14:16,293
Ms. Ko!

238
00:14:17,378 --> 00:14:19,254
The screen will crack.

239
00:14:28,889 --> 00:14:31,475
I won't abandon you guys.

240
00:14:31,558 --> 00:14:34,228
I'll come here to teach
even after an all-night shoot.

241
00:14:34,311 --> 00:14:36,605
-So brace yourselves, okay?
-Okay!

242
00:14:38,649 --> 00:14:39,692
Who's the lead actor?

243
00:14:39,775 --> 00:14:40,859
Who do you want it to be?

244
00:14:40,943 --> 00:14:42,027
Ji Seung-u!

245
00:14:42,111 --> 00:14:43,320
-Lee Gi-jun.
-Moon Seong-a?

246
00:14:43,404 --> 00:14:44,321
Cho Min-seong!

247
00:14:44,405 --> 00:14:45,739
Noh Kang-sik!

248
00:14:46,323 --> 00:14:47,157
Bingo.

249
00:14:47,741 --> 00:14:49,785
Of course, I'm fully aware how busy he is.

250
00:14:52,162 --> 00:14:53,872
He's the country's top actor, after all.

251
00:15:01,922 --> 00:15:03,132
I'll make you another cup.

252
00:15:04,299 --> 00:15:05,134
You know how it is.

253
00:15:05,759 --> 00:15:08,178
It's best that you get back to us quickly,
even if it's a pass.

254
00:15:08,262 --> 00:15:10,514
We can't wait long for Mr. Noh Kang-sik.

255
00:15:10,597 --> 00:15:11,932
Since it's a government-funded project,

256
00:15:12,016 --> 00:15:13,684
we have to submit
quarterly progress reports

257
00:15:13,767 --> 00:15:14,935
to get the payments.

258
00:15:16,145 --> 00:15:17,479
Yes, that's how it is.

259
00:15:17,563 --> 00:15:19,106
Please ask him one more time.

260
00:15:21,525 --> 00:15:23,318
Yes, thank you. Goodbye.

261
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:28,240
I'll send a screenplay over
and hear nothing back.

262
00:15:28,323 --> 00:15:31,910
This must be a big dilemma for you,
Gyeong-se.

263
00:15:32,786 --> 00:15:36,331
Hwang Dong-man needs to fail,
but Ko Hye-jin needs to do well.

264
00:15:36,415 --> 00:15:38,542
-How is that a dilemma?
-How is that a dilemma?

265
00:15:46,258 --> 00:15:47,760
You're saying Dong-man needs to fail.

266
00:15:49,720 --> 00:15:51,096
-No.
-Too late.

267
00:15:53,432 --> 00:15:55,809
You didn't bring him in to make money.

268
00:15:55,893 --> 00:15:57,061
You were pissed at Mr. Choi

269
00:15:57,144 --> 00:16:00,189
and just decided to do something else,
even if it's Hwang Dong-man's.

270
00:16:00,272 --> 00:16:02,274
You really think I'd just take on
a random screenplay?

271
00:16:03,442 --> 00:16:05,277
You read his screenplay.

272
00:16:05,360 --> 00:16:07,863
-So what if the writing is good?
-At least it's good!

273
00:16:13,285 --> 00:16:14,119
You hate it that much?

274
00:16:14,870 --> 00:16:17,247
You really hate seeing
Hwang Dong-man do well?

275
00:16:17,331 --> 00:16:19,333
Even though it means I'd do well too?

276
00:16:23,420 --> 00:16:26,048
You know the saying, "When your cousin
buys land, you turn green with envy"?

277
00:16:26,131 --> 00:16:27,758
I bet it only exists in Korea.

278
00:16:27,841 --> 00:16:29,468
It exists everywhere!

279
00:16:29,551 --> 00:16:31,053
Don't put down our people like that.

280
00:16:31,136 --> 00:16:33,514
I'm your wife, not your cousin!

281
00:16:33,597 --> 00:16:35,224
Your wife wants to buy some land!

282
00:16:35,307 --> 00:16:37,476
-We've always been poor anyway.
-For crying out loud.

283
00:16:37,559 --> 00:16:38,477
Cham, cham, cham.

284
00:16:42,439 --> 00:16:44,274
I'm going to become rich,

285
00:16:44,983 --> 00:16:46,735
so go ahead and stay poor.

286
00:16:59,248 --> 00:17:01,667
How do you fail to dodge it
every single time?

287
00:17:02,251 --> 00:17:04,086
I always turn to the right.

288
00:17:06,296 --> 00:17:07,756
Call it a voluntary punishment.

289
00:17:12,052 --> 00:17:16,431
<i>I talked to Hye-jin about crediting you</i>
<i>for the screenplay adaptation.</i>

290
00:17:18,642 --> 00:17:20,561
<i>That violates credit guidelines.</i>

291
00:17:21,186 --> 00:17:23,438
<i>You can't get credit</i>
<i>for simply giving notes.</i>

292
00:17:24,064 --> 00:17:25,858
<i>You should be the only one credited.</i>

293
00:17:26,859 --> 00:17:28,277
<i>But you wrote all those comments.</i>

294
00:17:29,736 --> 00:17:30,821
<i>It doesn't work that way.</i>

295
00:17:32,030 --> 00:17:33,115
<i>I wish</i>

296
00:17:33,699 --> 00:17:35,534
<i>I could just let the whole world know</i>

297
00:17:36,243 --> 00:17:38,370
<i>what kind of writer you are.</i>

298
00:17:39,121 --> 00:17:40,414
<i>If this turns out well,</i>

299
00:17:40,497 --> 00:17:43,125
<i>I'm going to go around telling people,</i>
<i>"Byeon Eun-a did this!"</i>

300
00:17:43,208 --> 00:17:46,253
<i>"Byeon Eun-a did this!"</i>

301
00:17:46,336 --> 00:17:49,673
<i>I'm going to cover the whole world</i>
<i>with Byeon Eun-a.</i>

302
00:17:55,679 --> 00:17:57,014
Hello!

303
00:17:57,097 --> 00:17:58,140
Hello.

304
00:18:07,274 --> 00:18:08,483
It's been a long time.

305
00:18:09,610 --> 00:18:10,861
I wanted to show my gratitude.

306
00:18:10,944 --> 00:18:12,779
Thanks to you, <i>My Mother</i> was a success.

307
00:18:12,863 --> 00:18:16,533
Ms. Oh prepared gifts
to thank everyone for their hard work.

308
00:18:16,617 --> 00:18:17,868
Oh my.

309
00:18:18,493 --> 00:18:20,329
What brings you here?
You didn't call ahead.

310
00:18:20,412 --> 00:18:22,789
I've been meaning to stop by,
but I only now got around to doing so.

311
00:18:22,873 --> 00:18:25,417
I didn't get to properly thank everyone
for their hard work.

312
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:27,794
You're the one who did all the hard work.

313
00:18:28,503 --> 00:18:29,421
This way, please.

314
00:18:29,504 --> 00:18:30,505
Oh, Director Ma.

315
00:18:31,757 --> 00:18:32,591
Mr. Choi.

316
00:18:34,259 --> 00:18:35,093
Who's this?

317
00:18:35,177 --> 00:18:37,763
Oh, this is Director Ma Jae-yeong.

318
00:18:37,846 --> 00:18:39,223
You read his screenplay,
<i>Knock knock knock</i>.

319
00:18:39,306 --> 00:18:40,307
I see.

320
00:18:40,933 --> 00:18:42,851
-Hello.
-Nice to meet you.

321
00:18:43,602 --> 00:18:45,187
I enjoyed your screenplay.

322
00:18:47,522 --> 00:18:48,482
Thank you.

323
00:18:51,401 --> 00:18:52,361
Let's go in.

324
00:19:01,245 --> 00:19:03,455
WE ARE SORRY TO SHARE THAT DIRECTOR
KIM SEONG-JUN'S MOTHER HAS PASSED AWAY

325
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:08,377
RECENTS

326
00:19:08,460 --> 00:19:10,087
LEE JUN-HWAN

327
00:19:12,047 --> 00:19:14,466
I just got a funeral notice
from Director Kim.

328
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:16,593
When are you going to the funeral hall?

329
00:19:17,844 --> 00:19:19,221
-There's more.
-Oh gosh.

330
00:19:19,304 --> 00:19:21,223
-Oh wow.
-Thank you.

331
00:19:21,306 --> 00:19:22,140
Thank you.

332
00:19:24,810 --> 00:19:27,062
Doesn't she have an insane presence?

333
00:19:27,145 --> 00:19:29,189
Her figure is amazing for her age.

334
00:19:29,273 --> 00:19:30,983
She's so generous.

335
00:19:31,066 --> 00:19:32,401
Oh Jeong-hui is the best.

336
00:19:33,860 --> 00:19:36,822
"People are all masses of emotion."

337
00:19:36,905 --> 00:19:38,240
I totally agree.

338
00:19:40,367 --> 00:19:42,244
How did you come up
with something like that?

339
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:48,875
You're right.

340
00:19:49,501 --> 00:19:52,504
If there were no such thing
as good parents or bad parents

341
00:19:52,587 --> 00:19:55,048
and all humans were born
from a bamboo shoot

342
00:19:55,132 --> 00:19:58,010
with no one to blame or resent,
this would be heaven.

343
00:19:59,094 --> 00:20:01,930
How did the gods miss something so simple?

344
00:20:07,436 --> 00:20:10,105
All the lines were words
I wanted to feel on my lips,

345
00:20:10,188 --> 00:20:11,606
so I read them out loud.

346
00:20:15,068 --> 00:20:16,737
There was real depth in your writing.

347
00:20:16,820 --> 00:20:20,282
You're more on the feminine side
than the masculine side, right?

348
00:20:21,908 --> 00:20:23,201
Do you have a woman's fortune?

349
00:20:23,285 --> 00:20:24,536
-Do you?
-Oh gosh, no.

350
00:20:25,037 --> 00:20:26,997
Why did you write the protagonist as male?

351
00:20:30,625 --> 00:20:33,337
The screenplay would work just fine
with a female protagonist.

352
00:20:34,171 --> 00:20:35,297
A woman fits better.

353
00:20:36,173 --> 00:20:37,507
You can't pull off

354
00:20:38,133 --> 00:20:39,885
this screenplay with just acting.

355
00:20:39,968 --> 00:20:42,679
You need an actor
who already carries that sentiment.

356
00:20:43,305 --> 00:20:46,850
Don't assume you can explain everything
and guide them on set.

357
00:20:47,434 --> 00:20:50,562
To do it justice, you need an actor
who understands the depth of your writing

358
00:20:50,645 --> 00:20:53,774
and can deliver every nuance
with microscopic precision.

359
00:20:54,358 --> 00:20:56,735
You'll have trouble if you cast an actor

360
00:20:56,818 --> 00:20:58,779
who makes every film their own
with their acting style.

361
00:21:00,364 --> 00:21:02,282
You clearly gave it your all.

362
00:21:02,366 --> 00:21:05,702
Can you handle
watching everything fall apart on set

363
00:21:05,786 --> 00:21:06,995
with an actor like that?

364
00:21:11,583 --> 00:21:13,460
I understood <i>Knock knock knock</i>

365
00:21:14,544 --> 00:21:15,754
to its core.

366
00:21:37,651 --> 00:21:39,736
<i>There's no need to find someone</i>
<i>to front the contract for you.</i>

367
00:21:39,820 --> 00:21:42,697
<i>I'll sign the contract under my name</i>
<i>and pay you your screenplay fee myself.</i>

368
00:21:50,705 --> 00:21:52,457
BYEON EUN-A

369
00:21:56,711 --> 00:21:57,921
<i>Don't leave me on read.</i>

370
00:21:58,004 --> 00:21:59,506
<i>Just say you got it.</i>

371
00:22:24,739 --> 00:22:27,826
I told you to go home. Why did you come?

372
00:22:27,909 --> 00:22:29,578
There's nothing to do there all alone.

373
00:22:30,662 --> 00:22:31,538
How are you feeling?

374
00:22:31,621 --> 00:22:33,206
I feel better than yesterday.

375
00:22:33,790 --> 00:22:34,624
Where's the caregiver?

376
00:22:35,458 --> 00:22:37,169
I told them to go eat.

377
00:22:38,670 --> 00:22:40,714
How much money are you spending?

378
00:22:41,339 --> 00:22:43,175
Surgery bills and now caregiver expenses…

379
00:22:43,258 --> 00:22:45,427
I'm spending it so you can live longer.

380
00:22:45,510 --> 00:22:46,511
Just live a long life.

381
00:22:46,595 --> 00:22:48,471
My goodness.

382
00:22:49,139 --> 00:22:50,640
By the way, who sent that?

383
00:22:52,726 --> 00:22:54,269
I thought it was you.

384
00:23:00,692 --> 00:23:02,068
WISHING YOU A SPEEDY RECOVERY
CEO PARK SANG-JIN

385
00:23:04,362 --> 00:23:06,990
NAME: BYEON SI-ON
GUARDIAN: GA SU-JA

386
00:23:29,763 --> 00:23:31,681
-Oh, hello.
-Hey, Yeong-su.

387
00:23:31,765 --> 00:23:32,682
-It's been a while.
-It has.

388
00:23:32,766 --> 00:23:33,892
-How have you been?
-Good.

389
00:23:34,935 --> 00:23:36,478
-Hello.
-Dong-man.

390
00:23:36,561 --> 00:23:38,021
I heard your film got greenlit.

391
00:23:38,104 --> 00:23:39,272
Oh, yes.

392
00:23:39,356 --> 00:23:42,108
Wow, your luck has finally turned.
Congratulations.

393
00:23:42,692 --> 00:23:43,860
Thank you.

394
00:23:49,157 --> 00:23:50,533
I heard the first two episodes are done.

395
00:23:51,159 --> 00:23:52,077
When do you start filming?

396
00:23:52,160 --> 00:23:53,787
How should I know that?

397
00:23:53,870 --> 00:23:55,205
If the director doesn't know, who does?

398
00:23:55,789 --> 00:23:57,499
I can't find any available actors.

399
00:23:57,582 --> 00:24:00,126
The good ones are booked solid
for the next couple of years.

400
00:24:00,710 --> 00:24:03,296
As long as the writing is good,
who cares about the actors?

401
00:24:03,380 --> 00:24:06,091
-Do calligraphers care what brush to use?
-They care. They care a lot.

402
00:24:06,174 --> 00:24:08,385
The more skilled they are,
the more expensive their brushes.

403
00:24:08,468 --> 00:24:10,262
Actors are everything in a movie.

404
00:24:12,597 --> 00:24:14,557
Then why'd you send your screenplay
to Noh Kang-sik?

405
00:24:16,476 --> 00:24:17,769
I respect actors

406
00:24:17,852 --> 00:24:21,982
like Noh Kang-sik and Oh Jeong-hui
whose names are now proper nouns.

407
00:24:22,065 --> 00:24:22,899
The rest are just…

408
00:24:22,983 --> 00:24:24,567
You mean common nouns.

409
00:24:25,277 --> 00:24:26,319
Common nouns.

410
00:24:26,403 --> 00:24:28,571
Names are already proper nouns.

411
00:24:28,655 --> 00:24:30,282
Whenever I say something, you just…

412
00:24:30,365 --> 00:24:32,492
Then stop talking like you know everything
when you're wrong.

413
00:24:32,575 --> 00:24:33,994
You just don't like me.

414
00:24:34,077 --> 00:24:35,036
Does anyone like you?

415
00:24:35,620 --> 00:24:36,705
Byeon Eun-a.

416
00:24:38,248 --> 00:24:39,624
Who likes you?

417
00:24:40,709 --> 00:24:41,876
Ko Hye-jin?

418
00:24:41,960 --> 00:24:44,379
She probably liked you
a long, long, long time ago.

419
00:24:45,922 --> 00:24:48,508
-Hey, say hello.
-It's been a while.

420
00:24:48,591 --> 00:24:49,551
-Hello.
-Hello.

421
00:24:49,634 --> 00:24:51,594
You two were inseparable in college.

422
00:24:51,678 --> 00:24:52,887
You still are, huh?

423
00:24:52,971 --> 00:24:56,141
Come on now, that was ages ago.

424
00:24:56,224 --> 00:24:57,726
These two are sworn enemies now.

425
00:25:02,230 --> 00:25:03,815
-Hello, sir.
-It's okay.

426
00:25:03,898 --> 00:25:05,025
-Sit down.
-Hello, sir.

427
00:25:05,734 --> 00:25:06,609
-Sit down.
-Hello.

428
00:25:12,073 --> 00:25:12,907
Hey.

429
00:25:13,408 --> 00:25:14,492
He beat up another one.

430
00:25:15,452 --> 00:25:16,286
Who?

431
00:25:17,412 --> 00:25:18,705
Cha Jeong-min.

432
00:25:19,372 --> 00:25:22,751
If his co-star acts well, he beats them
and knocks them off their game.

433
00:25:22,834 --> 00:25:25,420
There's no way he actually beat them up
in this day and age.

434
00:25:26,046 --> 00:25:28,631
Maybe he didn't full-on beat him up,
but he must've put his hands on him.

435
00:25:29,215 --> 00:25:30,091
You know?

436
00:25:33,219 --> 00:25:35,221
-There you are.
-Hey.

437
00:25:35,305 --> 00:25:37,640
-You can sit here.
-Thanks.

438
00:25:37,724 --> 00:25:39,351
Thank you for coming.

439
00:25:40,226 --> 00:25:41,061
Oh man.

440
00:25:41,144 --> 00:25:43,938
Gyeong-se, I hear you're doing
a streaming series.

441
00:25:44,689 --> 00:25:46,066
You never know until it starts.

442
00:25:46,149 --> 00:25:48,735
Hey, we need to start adapting now.

443
00:25:48,818 --> 00:25:50,278
The film era is basically over.

444
00:25:50,904 --> 00:25:52,405
Dong-man, I heard your film got greenlit.

445
00:25:53,156 --> 00:25:54,616
-Sorry?
-Your film.

446
00:25:55,367 --> 00:25:56,493
-Yes.
-That's good.

447
00:25:56,576 --> 00:25:57,952
All that waiting has paid off.

448
00:25:58,036 --> 00:26:00,205
-Take care of your health.
-Thank you.

449
00:26:03,458 --> 00:26:04,918
Your mother's well, right?

450
00:26:08,630 --> 00:26:09,589
Dong-man.

451
00:26:10,590 --> 00:26:12,592
You're at my mother's funeral.

452
00:26:16,137 --> 00:26:17,347
Did you just come for the food?

453
00:26:29,734 --> 00:26:31,403
That disrespectful punk.

454
00:26:31,486 --> 00:26:32,862
Come on, Kang-sik.

455
00:26:32,946 --> 00:26:34,489
Keep it friendly.

456
00:26:34,572 --> 00:26:35,824
"Keep it friendly"?

457
00:26:36,491 --> 00:26:37,867
Keep what friendly?

458
00:26:37,951 --> 00:26:41,579
Why should I keep it friendly
with someone who can't even act?

459
00:26:44,791 --> 00:26:48,586
He doesn't even have the basics.
Mainstream actor, my ass.

460
00:26:52,465 --> 00:26:53,299
Hello.

461
00:26:56,094 --> 00:26:57,303
We met not too long ago.

462
00:26:58,471 --> 00:26:59,556
In front of Agit.

463
00:27:01,683 --> 00:27:02,767
We shook hands.

464
00:27:07,230 --> 00:27:08,398
So what?

465
00:27:10,483 --> 00:27:12,402
I came to formally introduce myself.

466
00:27:15,321 --> 00:27:16,614
I'm Hwang Dong-man.

467
00:27:16,698 --> 00:27:17,615
Hwang Dong-man.

468
00:27:18,658 --> 00:27:21,035
I really want to make this film with you.

469
00:27:23,955 --> 00:27:24,789
Listen.

470
00:27:27,292 --> 00:27:29,419
There's a proper way to approach someone.

471
00:27:29,502 --> 00:27:32,213
Do I need to respond to everyone
who comes at me?

472
00:27:32,922 --> 00:27:34,674
I have an agency, you know.

473
00:27:35,925 --> 00:27:37,010
Oh.

474
00:27:37,093 --> 00:27:38,761
We sent this to your agency,

475
00:27:38,845 --> 00:27:39,929
but we haven't heard back.

476
00:27:41,681 --> 00:27:43,600
I really want to make this film with you.

477
00:27:44,184 --> 00:27:46,728
So you're basically saying,

478
00:27:46,811 --> 00:27:48,229
"I want to succeed."

479
00:27:48,313 --> 00:27:49,689
"Please help me."

480
00:27:49,772 --> 00:27:50,607
Why?

481
00:27:51,816 --> 00:27:53,943
Why should I help you?

482
00:27:56,404 --> 00:27:57,363
Do you know me?

483
00:27:59,115 --> 00:28:00,575
Have we worked on anything together?

484
00:28:02,660 --> 00:28:03,703
What films have you done?

485
00:28:05,497 --> 00:28:06,915
What films have you done?

486
00:28:12,420 --> 00:28:14,339
Well, nothing yet.

487
00:28:15,840 --> 00:28:18,384
This is my debut film.

488
00:28:20,303 --> 00:28:21,721
Know your place.

489
00:28:22,263 --> 00:28:23,723
I get your ambition,

490
00:28:23,806 --> 00:28:25,725
but I've got my own too.

491
00:28:25,808 --> 00:28:28,186
Do you know how hard I worked
to get to where I am?

492
00:28:28,269 --> 00:28:30,271
Why would I team up
with a nobody like you?

493
00:28:33,358 --> 00:28:35,109
If you want to work with me…

494
00:28:37,779 --> 00:28:38,863
move up

495
00:28:39,489 --> 00:28:40,448
to where I am.

496
00:28:42,283 --> 00:28:44,661
But for now, just stay where you are

497
00:28:44,744 --> 00:28:47,038
and stick to those on your level.

498
00:28:49,123 --> 00:28:51,918
Kids these days have too much ambition

499
00:28:52,001 --> 00:28:53,419
and just come at you.

500
00:28:56,840 --> 00:28:58,383
You should leave now.

501
00:29:02,846 --> 00:29:04,556
You have a lot of money.

502
00:29:05,765 --> 00:29:06,599
You want to borrow some?

503
00:29:06,683 --> 00:29:09,394
If I were set for life,

504
00:29:10,186 --> 00:29:12,397
I'd just take on whatever comes my way

505
00:29:14,065 --> 00:29:16,985
instead of getting into ego clashes
with much younger juniors.

506
00:29:18,987 --> 00:29:20,822
Why not just work with me

507
00:29:21,865 --> 00:29:23,366
before you get canceled
for beating a junior?

508
00:29:24,075 --> 00:29:25,076
-Go away.
-Get up.

509
00:29:25,159 --> 00:29:25,994
Get up.

510
00:29:27,662 --> 00:29:31,457
Nothing is more entertaining
than your mug!

511
00:29:31,541 --> 00:29:33,585
Let's see it full screen!

512
00:29:33,668 --> 00:29:35,420
-Not on a phone!
-You idiot!

513
00:29:35,503 --> 00:29:37,505
On a big screen!

514
00:29:37,589 --> 00:29:39,007
What the hell are you doing?

515
00:29:39,716 --> 00:29:40,550
Hey.

516
00:29:40,633 --> 00:29:42,844
<i>"Weather Maker"</i>?

517
00:29:42,927 --> 00:29:44,304
What are you, a god?

518
00:29:45,513 --> 00:29:46,347
Crazy bastard.

519
00:29:51,352 --> 00:29:52,186
Hey.

520
00:30:02,405 --> 00:30:03,865
He must be out of his mind.

521
00:31:06,803 --> 00:31:08,262
Isn't this pretty much the best

522
00:31:09,347 --> 00:31:11,599
for a directing team office?

523
00:31:11,683 --> 00:31:13,518
Given the rent, of course, it's the best.

524
00:31:13,601 --> 00:31:14,727
What a great view.

525
00:31:16,145 --> 00:31:17,855
What did DP Choi Gi-yeong say?

526
00:31:17,939 --> 00:31:19,273
-Is he on board?
-Yes.

527
00:31:19,357 --> 00:31:20,400
Nice.

528
00:31:20,483 --> 00:31:23,778
I used all the connections I had
to persuade him.

529
00:31:23,861 --> 00:31:24,737
Very well.

530
00:31:24,821 --> 00:31:26,280
We have a solid key crew.

531
00:31:27,031 --> 00:31:28,366
Now we just wait for it to become a hit.

532
00:31:29,409 --> 00:31:30,618
I'll do my best.

533
00:31:33,830 --> 00:31:34,747
So?

534
00:31:34,831 --> 00:31:36,082
Have you thought about it?

535
00:31:37,667 --> 00:31:38,793
About what Oh Jeong-hui said.

536
00:31:39,544 --> 00:31:40,420
Right.

537
00:31:42,797 --> 00:31:44,132
What do you think, Mr. Choi?

538
00:31:44,215 --> 00:31:46,592
The director's opinion matters the most.

539
00:31:50,263 --> 00:31:51,431
I think Noh Kang-sik

540
00:31:52,890 --> 00:31:54,475
might end up taking the lead on set,

541
00:31:54,559 --> 00:31:56,519
and I don't know if I can handle him.

542
00:31:57,145 --> 00:32:00,773
I think we need an actor
who fully understands the writing.

543
00:32:02,900 --> 00:32:04,235
And isn't Noh Kang-sik

544
00:32:05,319 --> 00:32:06,362
a bit of a risk?

545
00:32:07,155 --> 00:32:08,448
He's always getting into trouble.

546
00:32:15,747 --> 00:32:17,582
Let's put a hold
on Noh Kang-sik's contract.

547
00:32:19,751 --> 00:32:20,626
Okay.

548
00:32:21,252 --> 00:32:22,837
By the way, the screenplay fees

549
00:32:22,920 --> 00:32:24,756
will go to Ma Jae-yeong,
and he'll pay Yeong-sil.

550
00:32:24,839 --> 00:32:26,340
He said Yeong-sil suggested it.

551
00:32:27,300 --> 00:32:29,177
You really think Yeong-sil suggested that?

552
00:32:29,260 --> 00:32:30,845
It was probably Ma Jae-yeong.

553
00:32:32,096 --> 00:32:34,348
Oh Jeong-hui has an uncanny knack
for reading screenplays,

554
00:32:34,432 --> 00:32:37,060
and she said
the writing felt distinctly feminine.

555
00:32:37,143 --> 00:32:38,895
Yeong-sil wrote it.

556
00:32:39,854 --> 00:32:40,855
Just leave it be.

557
00:32:42,607 --> 00:32:44,567
Don't say a word about Yeong-sil,

558
00:32:45,318 --> 00:32:46,736
or it'll set Ma Jae-yeong off.

559
00:33:22,271 --> 00:33:24,190
How many names do you have?

560
00:33:25,358 --> 00:33:27,443
Byeon Si-on, Byeon Eun-a…

561
00:33:29,445 --> 00:33:30,488
and Yeong-sil.

562
00:33:33,616 --> 00:33:35,409
I can tell it's you.

563
00:33:36,244 --> 00:33:37,453
My name is Byeon Eun-a.

564
00:33:37,537 --> 00:33:38,913
Yeong-sil is a pseudonym.

565
00:33:38,996 --> 00:33:41,207
-Did you choose "Eun-a" as your name?
-Yes.

566
00:33:43,668 --> 00:33:45,628
Of all the names, why choose Eun-a?

567
00:33:45,711 --> 00:33:48,089
Of all the names, why choose Si-on?

568
00:33:48,881 --> 00:33:49,924
You named me, right?

569
00:33:50,508 --> 00:33:52,677
It sounds sophisticated and special.

570
00:33:53,928 --> 00:33:55,138
So?

571
00:33:55,805 --> 00:33:57,306
You're not even Christian.

572
00:33:58,266 --> 00:33:59,892
Why give your newborn a name

573
00:34:00,977 --> 00:34:03,229
that makes it sound like
they're forced to be special?

574
00:34:05,648 --> 00:34:06,899
Isn't it natural

575
00:34:07,525 --> 00:34:09,902
to want your child
to become someone special?

576
00:34:10,653 --> 00:34:12,405
Some parents name their child "Yeong-sil"

577
00:34:12,488 --> 00:34:14,240
so they'll have an easygoing life.

578
00:34:17,285 --> 00:34:18,995
Husband or child,

579
00:34:19,704 --> 00:34:23,332
everything tied to you had to be special
so you could stand out.

580
00:34:24,125 --> 00:34:26,085
But when you looked at
your quiet, slow child,

581
00:34:27,670 --> 00:34:30,256
your eyes suggested
things weren't quite right.

582
00:34:31,757 --> 00:34:33,092
I still remember that look.

583
00:34:34,260 --> 00:34:35,136
So you ended up

584
00:34:36,846 --> 00:34:38,681
giving up both your husband and child.

585
00:34:41,142 --> 00:34:42,977
It's ambition when you're capable.

586
00:34:43,978 --> 00:34:45,479
It's greed when you're not.

587
00:34:46,522 --> 00:34:48,858
If I'm clearly capable,

588
00:34:49,859 --> 00:34:52,153
why should I crush my ambitions
and hold myself back?

589
00:34:53,905 --> 00:34:55,489
You seem more fake to me.

590
00:34:56,657 --> 00:34:58,826
You have ambition. You're just killing it.

591
00:34:59,827 --> 00:35:01,329
You want people to know you're Yeong-sil.

592
00:35:01,954 --> 00:35:03,122
You want people to know

593
00:35:03,206 --> 00:35:05,124
how big your part was
in writing <i>Knock knock knock</i>.

594
00:35:05,750 --> 00:35:08,544
At the same time,
you're afraid people will tear you apart,

595
00:35:08,628 --> 00:35:12,840
so you hide behind a pseudonym
while feeding your ego.

596
00:35:12,924 --> 00:35:13,758
Right?

597
00:35:15,843 --> 00:35:19,430
I bet you're in hell right now
because you want to reveal yourself.

598
00:35:20,223 --> 00:35:22,934
And because you can't stand
Ma Jae-yeong taking all the credit.

599
00:35:26,604 --> 00:35:27,563
Just go for it.

600
00:35:28,231 --> 00:35:29,774
Tell everyone you're Yeong-sil

601
00:35:29,857 --> 00:35:31,108
and Oh Jeong-hui's daughter.

602
00:35:33,694 --> 00:35:35,738
I hear you've been
acting out of line with Mr. Choi.

603
00:35:36,781 --> 00:35:39,533
Would you really be able to act that way
if it weren't for me?

604
00:35:40,368 --> 00:35:43,079
"That's right,
keep giving me a hard time."

605
00:35:43,162 --> 00:35:45,957
"I'll make sure
you're utterly embarrassed later."

606
00:35:47,833 --> 00:35:49,502
You're saying that didn't cross your mind?

607
00:35:54,340 --> 00:35:56,217
You seem more fake to me.

608
00:36:22,201 --> 00:36:23,869
<i>You said you were going to be</i>
<i>really successful.</i>

609
00:36:24,453 --> 00:36:26,747
You told me not to cling to you then
and act like we're close.

610
00:36:27,707 --> 00:36:31,961
You told me not to leech off
your shining success.

611
00:36:33,379 --> 00:36:34,630
When will you ever shine

612
00:36:35,381 --> 00:36:37,008
if you hide behind a pseudonym?

613
00:36:47,184 --> 00:36:48,561
-Hi, Mi-ran.
-Hello.

614
00:36:48,644 --> 00:36:50,313
-Hello.
-Hello.

615
00:36:50,896 --> 00:36:51,981
So?

616
00:36:52,064 --> 00:36:54,233
-So--
-Aren't you going to say hi?

617
00:36:59,905 --> 00:37:00,906
Hello.

618
00:37:02,742 --> 00:37:04,076
So, what does he like about you?

619
00:37:04,160 --> 00:37:04,994
What?

620
00:37:07,121 --> 00:37:08,497
Hey, that's a secret.

621
00:37:08,581 --> 00:37:10,041
-I can't believe you asked me that.
-Come on.

622
00:37:10,124 --> 00:37:12,501
Tell me more.

623
00:37:12,585 --> 00:37:13,419
My gosh.

624
00:37:13,502 --> 00:37:15,671
-I'm so jealous.
-This is hilarious.

625
00:37:18,632 --> 00:37:20,468
I'm so jealous.

626
00:37:22,636 --> 00:37:24,096
Oh my gosh.

627
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:25,848
Sounds like it was fun.

628
00:37:25,931 --> 00:37:26,891
It was really fun.

629
00:37:26,974 --> 00:37:29,643
-It's a secret, okay?
-Okay, okay.

630
00:37:42,740 --> 00:37:44,033
Did you learn how to laugh yesterday?

631
00:37:45,451 --> 00:37:48,037
You laugh way too hard,
like you've never done it before.

632
00:37:48,704 --> 00:37:50,247
Do you laugh like that all the time?

633
00:37:50,748 --> 00:37:52,750
Because it seems like you only do it
when I show up.

634
00:37:54,085 --> 00:37:55,628
I always laugh a lot.

635
00:37:58,422 --> 00:37:59,256
Look.

636
00:37:59,340 --> 00:38:01,217
We're not on good terms,

637
00:38:01,300 --> 00:38:03,052
so shouldn't you behave yourself?

638
00:38:04,136 --> 00:38:06,639
Viewers are telling you to behave yourself
and stop acting out.

639
00:38:08,140 --> 00:38:09,600
Did I ever tell you

640
00:38:10,226 --> 00:38:12,103
that I almost became a shaman?

641
00:38:12,186 --> 00:38:13,938
I still see things, you know.

642
00:38:14,021 --> 00:38:16,065
You should really be careful

643
00:38:16,148 --> 00:38:17,483
because I see trouble in your future.

644
00:38:18,234 --> 00:38:21,737
I can see
you're just dying to cause trouble.

645
00:38:22,696 --> 00:38:24,949
You see, women who gain recognition
as someone's girlfriend

646
00:38:25,032 --> 00:38:30,162
instead of through their own work
eventually start acting overly confident,

647
00:38:30,246 --> 00:38:32,665
as if their boyfriend's name is their own.

648
00:38:39,547 --> 00:38:41,966
If you want to stay known
as someone's girlfriend,

649
00:38:42,758 --> 00:38:44,927
watch yourself
before things get out of hand.

650
00:38:52,351 --> 00:38:53,310
You know,

651
00:38:55,396 --> 00:38:59,608
I think people who claim
they can see things are so obnoxious.

652
00:39:01,277 --> 00:39:02,945
They should worry about their own future.

653
00:39:04,947 --> 00:39:07,199
There are rumors
in the Korean community in New York

654
00:39:08,075 --> 00:39:10,077
that Chairman Jang
is living with another woman.

655
00:39:11,328 --> 00:39:13,664
The only reason
anyone even acknowledges you

656
00:39:13,747 --> 00:39:15,166
is because you're Oh Jeong-hui's daughter.

657
00:39:16,584 --> 00:39:18,711
But I wonder who will
once she's out of your life.

658
00:39:21,547 --> 00:39:22,840
What does it feel like?

659
00:39:22,923 --> 00:39:24,925
Your father is living with another woman,

660
00:39:25,593 --> 00:39:28,929
but you're living under the same roof
with your stepmother.

661
00:39:29,763 --> 00:39:30,806
Oh, I see.

662
00:39:31,807 --> 00:39:34,643
Is that why you latch onto any man?

663
00:39:34,727 --> 00:39:36,479
Because you've got no one to love?

664
00:39:37,104 --> 00:39:39,607
You should be ashamed and embarrassed

665
00:39:39,690 --> 00:39:41,609
for latching onto
someone else's boyfriend.

666
00:39:45,571 --> 00:39:47,031
Let go. You'd better let go!

667
00:39:47,114 --> 00:39:49,700
I've dreamed about
grabbing you by the hair.

668
00:39:49,783 --> 00:39:51,327
Your hair feels freaking amazing!

669
00:39:51,410 --> 00:39:52,578
You crazy bitch.

670
00:39:55,456 --> 00:39:57,625
I grew up showered with love.

671
00:39:57,708 --> 00:40:00,586
My grandmother
goes to early morning prayers for me,

672
00:40:00,669 --> 00:40:02,379
gets me herbal tonics every season,

673
00:40:02,463 --> 00:40:04,131
and still dotes on me!

674
00:40:04,215 --> 00:40:06,592
-I've got so much love I can't hold it in!
-Don't do this!

675
00:40:06,675 --> 00:40:08,344
I'm overflowing with love!

676
00:40:10,888 --> 00:40:12,598
Is it a crime to have so much love?

677
00:40:12,681 --> 00:40:15,017
If I were you,
I'd be hugging me and crying,

678
00:40:15,100 --> 00:40:17,645
upset that I couldn't share that bastard,
Jeong Hyeon-u.

679
00:40:18,145 --> 00:40:20,523
You think you won? Are you happy now?

680
00:40:21,148 --> 00:40:23,859
You know what's so stupid
about what you believe?

681
00:40:24,735 --> 00:40:28,239
Thinking that loving more
makes you weaker.

682
00:40:28,322 --> 00:40:29,740
Idiot.

683
00:40:29,823 --> 00:40:31,367
That's why you're pathetic.

684
00:40:31,450 --> 00:40:33,244
You can't even tell the difference
between acting and reality,

685
00:40:33,327 --> 00:40:34,870
you crazy bitch!

686
00:40:34,954 --> 00:40:35,913
Hey.

687
00:40:35,996 --> 00:40:37,122
Let go.

688
00:40:37,915 --> 00:40:38,958
Hey.

689
00:40:40,167 --> 00:40:41,043
Goddamn it.

690
00:40:50,094 --> 00:40:50,970
Get in.

691
00:40:52,012 --> 00:40:54,974
I'm going to make you pay for this,
you crazy bitch!

692
00:40:55,057 --> 00:40:56,892
Go ahead and try, you dumbass bitch!

693
00:41:08,279 --> 00:41:11,073
We got the CCTV footage,
so we'll be seeing you soon.

694
00:41:11,156 --> 00:41:12,533
Okay. See you soon.

695
00:41:28,632 --> 00:41:29,800
Let's talk later.

696
00:41:51,905 --> 00:41:52,948
Let's go.

697
00:41:53,532 --> 00:41:54,491
Action!

698
00:42:16,597 --> 00:42:18,015
They can't release the CCTV footage.

699
00:42:19,600 --> 00:42:22,227
We collected plenty on them too
when they threatened to report you

700
00:42:22,311 --> 00:42:23,771
for stalking.

701
00:42:24,980 --> 00:42:26,065
They've got a lot of problems.

702
00:42:27,066 --> 00:42:28,776
Don't worry. They won't release it.

703
00:42:36,909 --> 00:42:38,827
Let's keep up
the celebrity mother-daughter angle

704
00:42:39,912 --> 00:42:40,871
to the very end.

705
00:43:00,265 --> 00:43:01,141
Jin-man.

706
00:43:01,850 --> 00:43:03,060
What's your purpose in life?

707
00:43:11,318 --> 00:43:12,319
To live lightly.

708
00:43:16,865 --> 00:43:18,951
Letting go of everything I can…

709
00:43:21,161 --> 00:43:23,455
not forming deep attachments to anything…

710
00:43:26,709 --> 00:43:27,835
and living lightly.

711
00:44:57,090 --> 00:44:57,925
<i>Everyone</i>

712
00:44:59,134 --> 00:45:00,761
<i>probably struggled to write these.</i>

713
00:45:03,222 --> 00:45:04,389
<i>But no one reads them…</i>

714
00:45:06,642 --> 00:45:07,976
<i>and they just get thrown away.</i>

715
00:45:10,229 --> 00:45:11,438
<i>What's the point of all this?</i>

716
00:45:12,773 --> 00:45:14,650
<i>Everything disappears in the end anyway.</i>

717
00:45:29,915 --> 00:45:30,958
<i>So why…</i>

718
00:45:34,169 --> 00:45:36,046
<i>are we living such hard lives…</i>

719
00:45:40,008 --> 00:45:42,010
<i>as if we'll never disappear?</i>

720
00:46:05,951 --> 00:46:06,785
<i>As if…</i>

721
00:46:08,370 --> 00:46:09,955
<i>we'll never disappear.</i>

722
00:46:13,083 --> 00:46:13,959
<i>As if…</i>

723
00:46:15,043 --> 00:46:16,044
<i>we'll never…</i>

724
00:46:17,254 --> 00:46:18,463
<i>disappear.</i>

725
00:47:07,679 --> 00:47:09,514
Hey, Dong-man!

726
00:47:11,600 --> 00:47:13,268
Hwang Dong-man!

727
00:47:14,227 --> 00:47:16,521
<i>Everything my voice reaches</i>

728
00:47:16,605 --> 00:47:17,439
<i>is mine.</i>

729
00:47:20,692 --> 00:47:22,235
Hey, Eun-a!

730
00:47:25,405 --> 00:47:27,199
Byeon Eun-a!

731
00:47:31,370 --> 00:47:33,455
Hey, Dong-man!

732
00:47:34,456 --> 00:47:36,416
Hey, Eun-a!

733
00:47:43,757 --> 00:47:46,009
He was going around acting like
he was going to work with Noh Kang-sik.

734
00:47:46,093 --> 00:47:47,636
-Serves him right.
-You punk.

735
00:47:47,719 --> 00:47:49,012
Are you Hwang Dong-man now?

736
00:47:49,596 --> 00:47:51,723
-Finding joy in others' failures?
-Didn't you know?

737
00:47:51,807 --> 00:47:53,433
I'm the Dong-man
of the freshman class of 2008.

738
00:47:54,768 --> 00:47:55,769
I'm so sick of this.

739
00:47:55,852 --> 00:47:58,689
I want everyone around me to do well.

740
00:47:58,772 --> 00:48:00,315
If I'm not going to make it anyway,

741
00:48:00,399 --> 00:48:03,193
the people around me should succeed
so I can pick up the crumbs.

742
00:48:04,152 --> 00:48:06,446
I like picking up the crumbs.

743
00:48:07,781 --> 00:48:10,075
Why doesn't anyone consider
picking up the crumbs?

744
00:48:10,158 --> 00:48:12,369
It's no good if none of us make it.

745
00:48:12,452 --> 00:48:16,206
Someone around me has to succeed
so I can live off it.

746
00:48:18,083 --> 00:48:18,917
Is she a good writer?

747
00:48:19,501 --> 00:48:21,628
-No.
-How could you say that?

748
00:48:21,712 --> 00:48:23,422
It's not my fault I can't write.

749
00:48:23,505 --> 00:48:25,841
But I can inspire instead.

750
00:48:25,924 --> 00:48:27,592
Put this crazy woman to use!

751
00:48:29,010 --> 00:48:30,637
Right, put her to use.

752
00:48:30,721 --> 00:48:32,973
Put her to good use!

753
00:48:33,056 --> 00:48:34,891
Put her to use.

754
00:48:34,975 --> 00:48:36,977
I have too much pride

755
00:48:37,060 --> 00:48:39,271
to live off picking up the crumbs.

756
00:48:39,354 --> 00:48:43,108
I'd rather sell my soul
and buy talent instead!

757
00:48:43,191 --> 00:48:46,194
Just sell an arm.
Why would you sell your soul?

758
00:48:46,278 --> 00:48:47,988
You don't even know if it exists.

759
00:48:48,071 --> 00:48:50,407
If it could be sold,
I'd sell it countless times.

760
00:48:51,032 --> 00:48:52,075
It's simple.

761
00:48:52,159 --> 00:48:54,494
Just sell an arm or don't.

762
00:48:54,578 --> 00:48:55,871
This is faster for Koreans.

763
00:48:55,954 --> 00:48:56,830
What about this?

764
00:48:57,789 --> 00:48:59,791
If giving up an arm

765
00:48:59,875 --> 00:49:02,252
makes you the world's top director,

766
00:49:02,919 --> 00:49:03,962
would you sell it or not?

767
00:49:05,380 --> 00:49:08,925
-The world's top director, huh?
-Top?

768
00:49:17,142 --> 00:49:18,185
I'd sell it.

769
00:49:18,268 --> 00:49:21,062
You said you'd live off
picking up the crumbs.

770
00:49:21,646 --> 00:49:23,690
That's because I have no talent.

771
00:49:23,774 --> 00:49:26,067
If I had talent, why would I do that?

772
00:49:30,155 --> 00:49:31,573
-Sell it?
-Did you see that look?

773
00:49:32,365 --> 00:49:34,743
What the heck?
Did she already sell her arm?

774
00:49:34,826 --> 00:49:35,702
Who would buy it?

775
00:49:36,286 --> 00:49:38,789
I could write a different version
of <i>Sister Vengeance</i>.

776
00:49:40,207 --> 00:49:41,917
You don't have to sell your arm.

777
00:49:43,001 --> 00:49:44,085
I read the script.

778
00:49:45,086 --> 00:49:47,464
The lines are much better
than Director Park's usual lame ones.

779
00:49:50,509 --> 00:49:51,927
Keep up the good work.

780
00:49:52,010 --> 00:49:56,473
I'd sell my arm if that's what it takes
to make him a huge success.

781
00:49:59,142 --> 00:50:02,020
He's the most adorable person ever.

782
00:50:08,777 --> 00:50:09,611
Do you want him?

783
00:50:17,202 --> 00:50:18,620
Goodness, Ms. Ko.

784
00:50:21,081 --> 00:50:22,165
No, it's not like that.

785
00:50:29,256 --> 00:50:30,549
There they are.

786
00:50:30,632 --> 00:50:32,509
I'm going to go now.

787
00:50:32,592 --> 00:50:34,845
-Wait up!
-Let's go together.

788
00:50:34,928 --> 00:50:36,596
-Let's go together.
-Hey, wait up.

789
00:50:37,264 --> 00:50:38,723
See you at home.

790
00:50:38,807 --> 00:50:40,559
You must have an early morning meeting.

791
00:51:06,126 --> 00:51:07,168
Hello.

792
00:51:10,171 --> 00:51:11,006
Oh.

793
00:51:11,798 --> 00:51:13,258
I'm Jang Mi-ran.

794
00:51:13,341 --> 00:51:16,177
The one who sang at your cousin's wedding.

795
00:51:21,892 --> 00:51:22,934
<i>It's like art</i>

796
00:51:24,519 --> 00:51:27,188
<i>Who knew this day would come?</i>
<i>It's like art</i>

797
00:51:29,900 --> 00:51:31,026
I guess you didn't see it.

798
00:51:35,405 --> 00:51:36,448
I just…

799
00:51:39,910 --> 00:51:41,494
I just wanted to see you.

800
00:51:44,331 --> 00:51:47,500
I wondered what kind of person
could write poems like that.

801
00:51:48,001 --> 00:51:50,837
SOMEWHERE, A WRONG REMAINS
POEMS BY HWANG JIN-MAN

802
00:52:06,853 --> 00:52:09,940
It's for uncovering the truth for me.

803
00:52:11,650 --> 00:52:12,901
A token of thanks, if you will.

804
00:52:46,142 --> 00:52:47,519
<i>I wash my face</i>

805
00:52:49,020 --> 00:52:50,355
<i>But something won't come off</i>

806
00:52:51,356 --> 00:52:53,066
<i>I trim my nails</i>

807
00:52:54,401 --> 00:52:56,361
<i>But something can't be trimmed</i>

808
00:52:58,655 --> 00:53:02,283
<i>I wring out a wet rag and wipe the floor</i>

809
00:53:04,202 --> 00:53:05,662
<i>But something won't wipe off</i>

810
00:53:07,414 --> 00:53:08,790
<i>Somewhere</i>

811
00:53:10,875 --> 00:53:11,710
<i>A wrong remains…</i>

812
00:53:13,503 --> 00:53:14,337
<i>A wrong remains…</i>

813
00:53:20,635 --> 00:53:22,220
<i>I set the table and sit down</i>

814
00:53:24,389 --> 00:53:25,890
<i>I see a glass</i>

815
00:53:31,062 --> 00:53:31,896
<i>Yes</i>

816
00:53:32,564 --> 00:53:33,523
<i>It's a drink</i>

817
00:53:57,839 --> 00:53:58,757
Hey, Ax.

818
00:54:00,050 --> 00:54:01,009
Get in here.

819
00:54:01,551 --> 00:54:04,429
Nobody has a problem
changing the protagonist to a woman.

820
00:54:04,512 --> 00:54:07,432
But you just had to dig in your heels
and make the meeting uncomfortable.

821
00:54:07,515 --> 00:54:09,601
Are the other producers morons?

822
00:54:09,684 --> 00:54:11,478
Do I have to rethink this
because you disagree?

823
00:54:11,561 --> 00:54:13,063
Even the director approved!

824
00:54:13,146 --> 00:54:14,522
Are you a writer?

825
00:54:15,190 --> 00:54:18,651
You went on about how <i>Knock knock knock</i>
isn't that kind of a story.

826
00:54:18,735 --> 00:54:20,361
You need to know when to stop.

827
00:54:21,237 --> 00:54:24,991
You review others' work long enough,
and you start thinking you're a writer.

828
00:54:25,700 --> 00:54:27,702
Do you know how writing is created?

829
00:54:28,203 --> 00:54:30,455
You want to try writing for a month
under Yeong-sil?

830
00:54:30,538 --> 00:54:33,208
You want a brutal reality check
on your skill level?

831
00:54:33,917 --> 00:54:36,044
Everyone wants to become a writer.

832
00:54:36,127 --> 00:54:39,923
People with no talent always go nuts
over someone else's good writing

833
00:54:40,006 --> 00:54:41,716
and act like they know everything,
as if they wrote it.

834
00:54:41,800 --> 00:54:43,802
They practically foam at the mouth.

835
00:54:43,885 --> 00:54:46,054
Just focus on your own work,

836
00:54:46,137 --> 00:54:49,557
and stop being a smart-ass
with that half-baked skill of yours!

837
00:54:49,641 --> 00:54:50,558
Got it, Ax?

838
00:54:56,272 --> 00:54:57,482
I'm Yeong-sil.

839
00:55:01,444 --> 00:55:02,320
It's me.

840
00:55:03,905 --> 00:55:04,906
I'm Yeong-sil.

841
00:55:09,869 --> 00:55:12,205
The writer Ma Jae-yeong
is so desperate to hide.

842
00:55:52,704 --> 00:55:54,622
NOH KANG-SIK

843
00:55:59,836 --> 00:56:01,671
<i>The person you are trying to reach</i>
<i>is unavailable.</i>

844
00:56:01,754 --> 00:56:03,047
<i>You will be redirected to voicemail after…</i>

845
00:56:03,131 --> 00:56:05,717
-This damn bastard.
-Stop calling.

846
00:56:06,968 --> 00:56:07,802
Kang-sik.

847
00:56:11,055 --> 00:56:12,307
This is the second time

848
00:56:14,017 --> 00:56:15,226
he offered a role and took it back.

849
00:56:20,857 --> 00:56:22,025
Hi, hi, hi!

850
00:56:22,108 --> 00:56:23,234
-Hey.
-You're here.

851
00:56:24,360 --> 00:56:25,445
Hello.

852
00:56:29,490 --> 00:56:30,366
I'll have a beer.

853
00:56:30,450 --> 00:56:31,701
Is that all the clothes he has?

854
00:56:41,211 --> 00:56:43,630
Let me tell you a story about this coat--

855
00:56:43,713 --> 00:56:45,506
You told that story a million times.

856
00:56:45,590 --> 00:56:47,467
-He's right.
-But he hasn't heard it yet.

857
00:56:47,550 --> 00:56:48,885
Just drink. Here you go.

858
00:56:49,594 --> 00:56:50,845
Hey!

859
00:56:51,721 --> 00:56:55,433
This right here took part in World War II.

860
00:56:56,809 --> 00:56:59,020
Do you see this bullet hole?

861
00:56:59,646 --> 00:57:04,317
I wear the clothes of a Russian soldier
who stood in the center of world history,

862
00:57:04,400 --> 00:57:06,319
where bullets flew all around him!

863
00:57:06,903 --> 00:57:11,991
This is a symbol of my intent
to step into the center of history myself!

864
00:57:12,075 --> 00:57:13,368
And my resolve!

865
00:57:13,451 --> 00:57:15,078
Which is why

866
00:57:15,161 --> 00:57:18,122
I wear this every single day.

867
00:57:18,748 --> 00:57:20,458
As long as I'm wearing this,

868
00:57:20,541 --> 00:57:22,544
it's impossible to hurt me

869
00:57:22,627 --> 00:57:25,046
with words like "low-level nobody."

870
00:57:25,129 --> 00:57:26,923
You can say anything you want,

871
00:57:27,006 --> 00:57:29,425
but nothing will scratch me.

872
00:57:31,594 --> 00:57:34,389
This right here stopped a bullet
in the middle of a war.

873
00:57:35,139 --> 00:57:38,810
Do you think mere human words
could hurt it?

874
00:57:41,479 --> 00:57:42,772
Good job.

875
00:57:42,855 --> 00:57:45,024
-Nicely done.
-Great job.

876
00:57:45,108 --> 00:57:46,693
-Well done.
-Here, have a drink.

877
00:57:46,776 --> 00:57:48,278
Hurry and eat first.

878
00:57:48,361 --> 00:57:50,113
There's a story
behind everything he carries.

879
00:57:50,780 --> 00:57:52,407
His laptop belonged to his late father.

880
00:57:52,490 --> 00:57:55,118
He gets his shoes from a shop
he's frequented for 20 years.

881
00:57:55,827 --> 00:57:57,453
He's addicted to stories.

882
00:57:58,121 --> 00:58:00,915
Life is nothing without stories.

883
00:58:00,999 --> 00:58:03,668
You might as well be dead without stories.

884
00:58:03,751 --> 00:58:06,004
He's more like a beggar than a director.

885
00:58:06,087 --> 00:58:06,921
Man.

886
00:58:07,547 --> 00:58:08,965
I can already see the set.

887
00:58:09,048 --> 00:58:12,385
I have zero interest in doing well.

888
00:58:12,468 --> 00:58:14,053
I'm going to fail completely

889
00:58:14,137 --> 00:58:16,806
and take pride
in simply having made a film.

890
00:58:16,889 --> 00:58:19,183
And I'm going to wish everyone
who lost money investing in me

891
00:58:19,267 --> 00:58:23,771
great success and wealth
for generations to come

892
00:58:23,855 --> 00:58:26,441
and pray for them every day.

893
00:58:28,026 --> 00:58:30,278
As for the ones who totally blew me off,

894
00:58:30,361 --> 00:58:32,155
I hope they crash and burn!

895
00:58:37,118 --> 00:58:39,746
I'm going to pray really hard.

896
00:58:39,829 --> 00:58:41,164
"Please fail."

897
00:58:41,247 --> 00:58:42,290
"Please fail."

898
00:58:42,373 --> 00:58:44,459
I'm going to pray for their failure,

899
00:58:44,542 --> 00:58:45,918
and even perform a shamanistic ritual!

900
00:58:46,002 --> 00:58:49,339
I may not perform a shamanistic ritual
for my own success,

901
00:58:50,089 --> 00:58:52,800
but I'll do it for others' failures.

902
00:58:52,884 --> 00:58:54,469
I'll take out a loan if I have to!

903
00:58:54,552 --> 00:58:55,762
Stop already, you punk!

904
00:58:55,845 --> 00:58:57,513
Just stop, okay?

905
00:58:57,597 --> 00:58:59,265
-That's enough.
-Why?

906
00:58:59,349 --> 00:59:00,975
-It's fun.
-Okay, okay.

907
00:59:01,059 --> 00:59:02,268
-It's fine as long as it's fun.
-All right.

908
00:59:02,352 --> 00:59:04,312
This is the story of my life.

909
00:59:04,395 --> 00:59:06,356
Okay, I got it. Just lower your voice.

910
00:59:07,357 --> 00:59:09,525
-I suddenly want to do it.
-You like blockbuster hits?

911
00:59:10,276 --> 00:59:12,278
-What's the point of being rich
-His film.

912
00:59:12,362 --> 00:59:14,238
if your life story sucks?

913
00:59:14,322 --> 00:59:17,867
If I had that kind of money,
I'd totally live in style!

914
00:59:18,493 --> 00:59:19,494
What was your name again?

915
00:59:20,161 --> 00:59:22,205
It's Hwang Dong-man!

916
00:59:23,289 --> 00:59:24,332
I'll work with you.

917
00:59:28,252 --> 00:59:29,754
Let's do it, Hwang Dong-man.

918
00:59:30,546 --> 00:59:31,714
What are you doing, Kang-sik?

919
00:59:31,798 --> 00:59:33,841
You haven't even read the screenplay.

920
00:59:33,925 --> 00:59:35,593
I don't have to. He's too obvious.

921
00:59:36,511 --> 00:59:38,721
It'll run me into the ground,
and I'll go through hell.

922
00:59:40,223 --> 00:59:42,350
Let me try writing a different life story.

923
00:59:42,934 --> 00:59:43,935
Let's just go for it.

924
00:59:45,061 --> 00:59:46,688
Let's team up with a guy like him

925
00:59:47,772 --> 00:59:49,065
and just go for it.

926
00:59:53,695 --> 00:59:56,614
-Hold on.
-Please don't, sir.

927
00:59:59,409 --> 01:00:00,243
I'm serious.

928
01:00:01,786 --> 01:00:02,870
I'll do it.

929
01:00:03,496 --> 01:00:04,330
Let's do it.

930
01:00:05,456 --> 01:00:06,874
I'll take half my usual fee.

931
01:00:10,461 --> 01:00:12,171
It's government-funded, right?

932
01:00:13,631 --> 01:00:14,549
So half my usual fee.

933
01:00:15,466 --> 01:00:16,759
Strike while the iron's hot, right?

934
01:00:17,468 --> 01:00:18,428
Should we sign a contract?

935
01:00:18,511 --> 01:00:19,470
Let's do that.

936
01:00:20,680 --> 01:00:21,556
Bring the contract.

937
01:00:38,364 --> 01:00:39,824
Ms. Ko, slow down. You'll get hurt.

938
01:00:39,907 --> 01:00:41,784
Hurry up. Come on.

939
01:00:42,285 --> 01:00:43,995
ACTOR CONTRACT

940
01:00:48,416 --> 01:00:49,417
Sir.

941
01:00:50,042 --> 01:00:51,377
You're drunk right now.

942
01:00:52,587 --> 01:00:53,588
Don't sign it.

943
01:01:11,773 --> 01:01:14,776
NOH KANG-SIK

944
01:01:22,200 --> 01:01:24,160
Good for you!

945
01:01:26,245 --> 01:01:27,246
Thank you, sir!

946
01:01:55,441 --> 01:01:56,526
Come on.

947
01:02:05,368 --> 01:02:06,202
Thank you.

948
01:02:09,330 --> 01:02:10,706
Let's step into the center

949
01:02:11,332 --> 01:02:12,166
of history.

950
01:02:13,626 --> 01:02:14,460
Okay.

951
01:02:36,774 --> 01:02:38,568
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

952
01:02:56,669 --> 01:02:58,546
Make it big, Hwang Dong-man!

953
01:02:58,629 --> 01:03:02,216
Now that Noh Kang-sik is on board,
I'm worried it might be too successful.

954
01:03:03,676 --> 01:03:06,554
Let's keep the fact that you're Yeong-sil
just between you and me.

955
01:03:06,637 --> 01:03:09,265
<i>I heard the writer</i>
<i>is against casting me in the role.</i>

956
01:03:09,348 --> 01:03:11,434
I'd like to know why you're against it,

957
01:03:12,018 --> 01:03:13,352
Ms. Yeong-sil.

958
01:03:13,436 --> 01:03:16,397
Who the hell are you
to object to casting Oh Jeong-hui?

959
01:03:16,480 --> 01:03:18,733
<i>You even went behind my back</i>
<i>and told Mr. Choi that you're Yeong-sil.</i>

960
01:03:18,816 --> 01:03:19,942
Call them now!

961
01:03:20,026 --> 01:03:21,694
-Let go of me!
-Hey.

962
01:03:21,777 --> 01:03:24,488
Call the reporters,
but at least wait until after my film!

963
01:03:25,072 --> 01:03:26,824
Wait until I'm done with my film!

964
01:03:26,908 --> 01:03:31,829
Subtitle translation by: Jenny Kim

